<item>
            <title>[BATCH-1526] Memory leak in web deployments because ThreadLocal is not nulled out in ChunkMonitor</title>
                <link>https://jira.spring.io/browse/BATCH-1526</link>
                <project id="10090" key="BATCH">Spring Batch</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The Tomcat leak detection in 6.0.24 caught this one: it&apos;s a tiny leak but the thread local in ChunkMonitor is not nulled out so re-deployment of a web application can result in a memory leak.  Tomcat fixes it (from 6.0.24) so it&apos;s probably not a big deal for existing users.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
